- Based on the newly issued NOTAM for the Tehran Flight Information Region (Tehran FIR), restrictions and closure of airports in western Iran have been extended until the morning of May 25, 2026.
- According to NOTAM code A1010/26, all airports in the western part of the Tehran FIR are closed, with only a few specified airports allowed limited operations from sunrise to sunset.
- The listed limited-operation airports on the page are Tabriz, Kermanshah, Ahvaz, Shiraz, Yazd, Kerman, Kish, and Abadan.
- The page says all previous flight permissions were canceled and airlines must obtain new authorization from the Civil Aviation Organization to conduct IFR passenger flights.
- The page states validity from Friday, May 22, 2026, at 00:16 Iran time to Monday, May 25, 2026, at 12:00 noon Iran time.
- It attributes the extension to security situation and military control over western Iran's airspace, and states the country's airspace had not returned to normal conditions.

Source-chain note: This is a media report, not the official NOTAM record. It corroborates the Notamify raw NOTAM and provides alleged A1010/26 timing before the A1015/26 replacement.